verbose_text: Because of the limited number of Annexin V-FITC positive cells, it was easy to discern from Fig. XREF_FIG B & D death of BCPAP cells as necroptosis or necrosis rather than typical apoptosis, which was possibly caused by autofluorescence of Obatoclax.
